1.00	Tin-glazed	Tin-glazing	Tin-glazing is the process of giving ceramic items a tin-based glaze which is white, glossy and opaque, normally applied to red or buff earthenware. The opacity and whiteness of tin glaze make it valued by its ability to decorate with colour.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Chinese_white_ware_and_Iraqi_earthenware_bowls_9th_10th_century_both_found_in_Iraq.jpg/350px-Chinese_white_ware_and_Iraqi_earthenware_bowls_9th_10th_century_both_found_in_Iraq.jpg
